cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.CV

The paper proposes a novel meta-heuristic algorithm for optimization problems and tests its performance on benchmark functions. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), or Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed algorithm is compared to other meta-heuristics, indicating that it could also belong to the Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-category. Finally, the paper applies the proposed algorithm to a real-world problem of fake review detection, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
